  <li><strong>10 percent: control board fault.</strong> $640 to $920 typical.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Repair-vs-replace economics on Sub-Zero</h2>

<p>The repair-vs-replace conversation on Sub-Zero is different from mid-tier brands. A Sub-Zero BI-42 at year 12 with a single-compressor failure: replacement cost $2,400 to $3,200; current new unit installed $14,000 to $16,000. Repair is the obvious answer. Same logic at year 15 with a defrost fault and a gasket replacement combined: $1,200 to $1,800 of work, vs $14,000 replacement. We service Sub-Zero through year 18 to 20+ as standard practice; the compressor lifetime warranty (12 years on most generations) extends actual service life accordingly.</p>

<p>The replace conversation only enters at year 18+ when multiple sealed-system circuits have been replaced and a third compressor failure is developing on the original chassis. Even then, it's usually the customer choosing to refresh aesthetics with a new unit, not the math forcing the decision.</p>

